[[sn:Tsuchimikado Hisanaga]] [[ja:土御門久脩]]

{{Infobox noble | name = Tsuchimikado Hisanaga | image = | caption = | era = [[:en:Azuchi–Momoyama period|Azuchi–Momoyama period]] - [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]] | birth_date = [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 3 ([[:en:1560|1560]]) | death_date = [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 2, [[:en:January 18|January 18 (old calendar)]] ({{ill|February 24, 1625|ja|1625th year 2月24日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 24, 1625|qq=}}) | titles = {{ill|Junior Third Rank|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Third Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Third Rank|qq=}}, {{ill|Counselor who does not participate|ja|非参議|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Counselor who does not participate|qq=}}, {{ill|Head of the Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head of the Onmyōryō|qq=}}, {{ill|Sakyo no Daibu|ja|左衛門佐|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakyo no Daibu|qq=}} | served = [[:en:Emperor Ōgimachi|Emperor Ōgimachi]], [[:en:Emperor Go-Yōzei|Emperor Go-Yōzei]], [[:en:Emperor Go-Mizunoo|Emperor Go-Mizunoo]] | clans = {{ill|Abe clan|ja|阿倍氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Abe clan|qq=}}, {{ill|Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado family|qq=}} | father = {{ill|Tsuchimikado Arihisa|ja|土御門有脩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado Arihisa|qq=}} | siblings = {{ill|Tsuchimikado Hisanaga|ja|久脩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado Hisanaga|qq=}}, Wife of {{ill|Kanjūji Harutoyo|ja|勧修寺晴豊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanjūji Harutoyo|qq=}} | spouse = Daughter of {{ill|Mitsufuchi Harukazu|ja|三淵晴員|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mitsufuchi Harukazu|qq=}} | children = {{ill|Tsuchimikado Yasunaga|ja|泰重|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado Yasunaga|qq=}}, {{ill|Kurahashi Yasuyoshi|ja|倉橋泰吉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurahashi Yasuyoshi|qq=}}, {{ill|Itsutsuji Seichu|ja|五辻斉仲|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Itsutsuji Seichu|qq=}} }}
'''Tsuchimikado Hisanaga''' (土御門 久脩) was a {{ill|Kuge|ja|Kugyō|1=Kugyō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuge|13=User:Immanuelle/Kugyō|qq=}} (court noble) and [[:en:Onmyōji|Onmyōji]] who lived during the [[:en:Azuchi–Momoyama period|Azuchi–Momoyama period]] and the early [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]]. He was the son of {{ill|Tsuchimikado Arihisa|ja|土御門有脩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado Arihisa|qq=}}, the head of the {{ill|Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyōryō|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=}}. Hisanaga attained the Rank of {{ill|Junior Third Rank|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Third Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Third Rank|qq=}} and held positions such as {{ill|Hisanagi|ja|非参議|lt=Non-councilor|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Non-councilors|qq=}} and {{ill|Head of the Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head of the Onmyōryō|qq=}}.
== Biography ==
=== Early Life === Tsuchimikado Hisanaga was educated in {{ill|Tenmondō|ja|天文道|1=Tenmondō (astrology)|lt=Tenmondō|qq= (astrology)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmondō|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmondō (astrology)|qq=}} (astronomy) and {{ill|Rekidō|ja|暦道|1=Rekidō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rekidō|13=User:Immanuelle/Rekidō|qq=}} (calendar science) from a young age. In [[:en:Genki (era)|Genki]] 3 (1572), he came of age. At 14 years old, he was appointed as {{ill|Head of the Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head of the Onmyōryō|qq=}} on {{ill|December 28, 1573|ja|天正元年12月28日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/December 28, 1573|qq=}}.
=== Adoption into Kadenokōji Family === Hisanaga was briefly adopted into the {{ill|Kadenokōji family|ja|勘解由小路家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kadenokōji family|qq=}} as the family lacked an heir. However, after the death of his father in [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 5 (1577), he returned to the {{ill|Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado family|qq=}} and resumed his birthright.
=== Service and Achievements === Hisanaga served under leaders such as [[:en:Oda Nobunaga|Oda Nobunaga]], [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]], and [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyasu|Tokugawa Ieyasu]]. He played a significant role in the {{ill|calendar reform debates of the Tenshō period|ja|天正の改暦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/calendar reform debates of the Tenshō period|qq=}} and later became involved in the administrative and ritual duties of the {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|徳川幕府|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|qq=}}.
In [[:en:Bunroku|Bunroku]] 4 (1595), Hisanaga was temporarily exiled to [[:en:Owari Province|Owari Province]] due to his alleged involvement in political conflicts.
=== Later Life === He returned to Kyoto in [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 5 (1600) and regained favor, continuing his work in the {{ill|Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyōryō|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=}}. His contributions to court and shogunate rituals, including those for imperial successions and shogunate ceremonies, solidified his legacy.
Hisanaga passed away on {{ill|February 24, 1625|ja|1625th year 2月24日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 24, 1625|qq=}}.
== Family and Descendants == Hisanaga's descendants continued to play significant roles in the {{ill|Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado family|qq=}} lineage and in other noble families. However, the direct male lineage of [[:en:Abe no Seimei|Abe no Seimei]] is believed to have ended.
