'''Tsuchimikado Hisanaga''' (土御門 久脩) was a {{ill|Kuge|ja|Kugyō|1=kugyō|2=ja|3=公卿|1=Kugyō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuge|13=User:Immanuelle/Kugyō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q3138036}} (court noble) and [[:en:Onmyōji|Onmyōji]] who lived during the [[:en:Azuchi–Momoyama period|Azuchi–Momoyama period]] and the early [[:en:Edo period|Edo period]]. He was the son of {{ill|Tsuchimikado Arihisa|ja|土御門有脩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado Arihisa|qq=|1=Tsuchimikado Arinaga|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11423481}}, the head of the {{ill|Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyōryō|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=}}. Hisanaga attained the Rank of {{ill|Junior Third Rank|ja|従三位|1=Junior Third Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Third Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Third Rank|qq=}} and held positions such as {{ill|Hisanagi|ja|非参議|lt=Non-councilor|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Non-councilors|qq=}} and {{ill|Head of the Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head of the Onmyōryō|qq=|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11658275}}.

== Biography ==

=== Early Life ===
Tsuchimikado Hisanaga was educated in {{ill|Tenmondō|ja|天文道|1=Tenmondō (astrology)|lt=Tenmondō|qq= (astrology)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmondō|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmondō (astrology)|qq=}} (astronomy) and {{ill|Rekidō|ja|暦道|1=Rekidō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rekidō|13=User:Immanuelle/Rekidō|qq=}} (calendar science) from a young age. In [[:en:Genki (era)|Genki]] 3 (1572), he came of age. At 14 years old, he was appointed as {{ill|Head of the Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽頭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Head of the Onmyōryō|qq=|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11658275}} on {{ill|December 28, 1573|ja|天正元年12月28日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/December 28, 1573|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.

=== Adoption into Kadenokōji Family ===
Hisanaga was briefly adopted into the {{ill|Kadenokōji family|ja|勘解由小路家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kadenokōji family|qq=}} as the family lacked an heir. However, after the death of his father in [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 5 (1577), he returned to the {{ill|Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado family|qq=}} and resumed his birthright.

=== Service and Achievements ===
Hisanaga served under leaders such as [[:en:Oda Nobunaga|Oda Nobunaga]], [[:en:Toyotomi Hideyoshi|Toyotomi Hideyoshi]], and [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyasu|Tokugawa Ieyasu]]. He played a significant role in the {{ill|calendar reform debates of the Tenshō period|ja|天正の改暦|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/calendar reform debates of the Tenshō period|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and later became involved in the administrative and ritual duties of the {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|1=Tokugawa shogunate|2=ja|3=江戸幕府|ja|徳川幕府|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 江戸幕府}}.

In [[:en:Bunroku|Bunroku]] 4 (1595), Hisanaga was temporarily exiled to [[:en:Owari Province|Owari Province]] due to his alleged involvement in political conflicts.

=== Later Life ===
He returned to Kyoto in [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 5 (1600) and regained favor, continuing his work in the {{ill|Onmyōryō|ja|陰陽寮|1=Yin-Yang Bureau|2=ja|3=陰陽寮|4=fr|5=Bureau d'Onmyō|6=zh|7=阴阳寮|8=ko|9=음양료|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onmyōryō|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang Bureau|qq=}}. His contributions to court and shogunate rituals, including those for imperial successions and shogunate ceremonies, solidified his legacy.

Hisanaga passed away on {{ill|February 24, 1625|ja|1625th year 2月24日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 24, 1625|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.

== Family and Descendants ==
Hisanaga's descendants continued to play significant roles in the {{ill|Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado family|qq=}} lineage and in other noble families. However, the direct male lineage of [[:en:Abe no Seimei|Abe no Seimei]] is believed to have ended.

